July 18 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* State-backed Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc <RBS.L> is shuttering a distressed-debt unit as it continues to shrink its investment bank, Bloomberg reported, citing three people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL6N0PS769]  * Blackstone Group LP <BX.N>, KKR & Co LP <KKR.N> and TPG Capital LP [TPG.UL] are in talks to settle a U.S. lawsuit accusing them of conspiring not to outbid each other and other buyout firms on takeovers of companies, two people familiar with the matter said on Thursday. [ID:nL2N0PT00G]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]